}}{{TIDTOC|adapter}} ==Overview== 748566-005 is the model info on the MAC / model label on the top side of the board. In full, for this particular card, it reads '''00D0B74835A4 03013 748566-005'''. :An encryption export warning sticker <small("Unlawful to export outside the U.S. or Canada except under an approved U.S. Dept. of Commerce export license or applicable license exception.")</small> is immediately under the MAC / model label. There is a '''Fujitsu''' 3DES HW acclerator chip on-board. The text on the chip reads... :*<FJ logo> '''JAPAN''' :*'''750387-002''' :*'''N82594ED 3DES''' :*'''MB87L301BPB-MP''' :*'''9935 U15''' The '''Intel''' 82559C chip is marked with... :*The big '''Intel i''' logo on the left side :*'''GD82559C''' :*'''L933IF65''' :*'''(M)(C)'99''' :*'''KOREA''' "PB743262-005" (PB code [??]: 743262-005) and "MP743260-005" (MP code [??]: 743260-005) is etched onto the bottom of the board (along with some '''KALEX''' text).
There is no '''Intel''' logo anywhere on the card except on the Ethernet controller..
